snippet: The Islamic State of Iraq and Syria has intensified its attacks across Iraq as political rivals work to form a new government.
abstract: United Nations reports that violence claimed lives of 799 Iraqis in May, highest monthly death toll in 2014; number points to challenges Iraq's government faces as it struggles to contain sectarian violence.
lead_paragraph: The Islamic State of Iraq and Syria has intensified its attacks across Iraq as political rivals work to form a new government.
